THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 386.320 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 386.320 1. Each member of the board of trustees of a school
3 district in a county whose population is less than 20,000 must
4 receive a salary of $250 per month.
5 2. Each member of the board of trustees of a school district in a
6 county whose population is 20,000 or more but less than 100,000
7 must receive a salary of $400 per month.
8 3. Each member of the board of trustees of a school district in a
9 county whose population is 100,000 or more but less than 700,000
10 must receive a salary of $750 per month.
11 4. Each member of the board of trustees of a school district in
12 a county whose population is 700,000 or more must receive an
13 annual salary that is equal to the annual salary for a county
14 commissioner in the county set forth in NRS 245.043.
15 5. A member of the board of trustees of a school district who
16 receives a salary pursuant to this section may:
17 (a) Donate all or a part of the monthly salary that he or she
18 receives to a school within the school district or to the school
19 district; or
20 (b) In lieu of making a donation after the member receives the
21 salary, request that all or a part of his or her monthly salary be paid
22 directly to a school within the school district or to the school
23 district.
24 [5.] 6. The board of trustees may hire a stenographer to take
25 the minutes of the meetings of the board of trustees, and the
26 stenographer may be paid a reasonable fee for each meeting
27 attended.
28 Sec. 2. The amendatory provisions of this act apply only to a
29 member of the board of trustees of a school district who is elected or
30 appointed to a term of office that begins on or after January 1, 2027,
31 including, without limitation, a member who is reelected or
32 reappointed to a term that begins on or after that date.
33 Sec. 3. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
34 additional expenses of a local government that are related to the
35 provisions of this act.
36 Sec. 4. This act becomes effective on January 1, 2027.
